  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-69118ea6e6df",
  "content": "let chunk_vec: Vec<String> = chunk.to_vec();\n            let embeddings = engine.embed_batch(&chunk_vec).await?;\n            for (i, embedding) in embeddings.into_iter().enumerate() {\n                entries[embedded_count + i].embedding = Some(embedding);\n            }\n            embedded_count += chunk.len();\n            println!(\"  embedded {}/{}\", embedded_count, entries.len());\n        }\n\n        // Insert\n        for entry in &entries {\n            store.insert(entry).await?;\n        }\n        println!(\"  {} entries stored\", entries.len());\n    }\n\n    println!(\"\\nWorkspace ingest complete.\");\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Wire the handler in main.rs**\n\nReplace `todo!()` in `WorkspaceCommands::Ingest`:\n\n```rust\nWorkspaceCommands::Ingest { repo, fresh } => {\n    let root = std::env::current_dir()?;\n    workspace::ingest_workspace(&root, repo.as_deref(), fresh).await?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Make existing `corvia ingest` workspace-aware**\n\nModify `cmd_ingest` in main.rs to detect workspace mode when no path is given. Since `ingest` currently requires a path argument, change the clap definition to make path optional:\n\nChange the Ingest variant in `Commands`:\n```rust\n    /// Ingest a repository (or all workspace repos if no path given)\n    Ingest {\n        /// Path to repository (optional in workspace mode)",
